On March 30, 2022, President Joseph R. Biden Jr. announced the continuation of the national emergency declared on April 1, 2015, regarding malicious cyber-enabled activities originating from outside the United States. This declaration was made in response to the ongoing threat these activities pose to national security, foreign policy, and the economy of the United States. The national emergency will remain in effect for another year, in accordance with the National Emergencies Act. This announcement was published in the Federal Register and transmitted to Congress.